<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Defend" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Defend,</orth> 1) trans. a) to protect from violence or injury: <cit><quote>what thorns the growing rose --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 492" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 492</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. luc 492" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 492</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wiv 3.3.126" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. III, 3, 126</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 5.88" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. V, 88</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 1.242" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 242</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.3.88" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 88</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.2.113" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 2, 113</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.7.38" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 7, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.213" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 213</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.2.284" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 2, 284</bibl> etc. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.1.219" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 1, 219</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 2.2.158" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. II, 2, 158</bibl> <cit><quote>(what shall d. the interim?).</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.335" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 2, 335</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.6.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 6, 101</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.2.30" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 2, 30</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.1.135" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 135</bibl>. <cit><quote>O d. me!</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 2.2.92" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. II, 2, 92</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>O God, d. me!</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 4.1.78" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado IV, 1, 78</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.331" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 331</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 5.3.117" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 V, 3, 117</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.3.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. II, 3, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 5.3.256" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 3, 256</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.2.95" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 2, 95</bibl>. <cit><quote>God d. the right!</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.216" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 216</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.101" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 101</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.3.55" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 3, 55</bibl>. <cit><quote>so d. thee heaven,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.15" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 15</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.15" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 15</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.15" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 15</bibl> <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.373" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 373</bibl> (Ff <emph>forgive</emph>). <cit><quote>angels and ministers of grace d. us!</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.4.39" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 4, 39</bibl></cit>.<lb />Reflectively: <cit><quote>d. thyself,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.4.34" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 4, 34</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.179" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 179</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.1.45" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 1, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.5.19" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 5, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.2.94" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 2, 94</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 2.1.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 1, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.3.203" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 3, 203</bibl>.
<lb />Followed by <emph>from</emph>: <cit><quote>d. me from what is past,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1684" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1684</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>heavens d. me from that Welsh fairy,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.85" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 5, 85</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.1.268" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. III, 1, 268</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.2.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 2, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.1.187" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 1, 187</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.141" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.141" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 141</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.5.5" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 5, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.3.22" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 3, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.114" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 114</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 5.4.23" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. V, 4, 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.175" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 175</bibl>.
<lb />b) to maintain by force or by argument, to secure: <cit><quote>fair fall the wit that can so well d. her,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 472" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 472</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I lost the ring --ing it,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 5.178" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. V, 178</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mv 5.178" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. V, 178</bibl> <cit><quote>let this d. my loyalty,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.1.67" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 1, 67</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>which in myself I boldly will d.</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 1.1.67" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 1, 67</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>when Helen is --ed,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 2.2.158" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 2, 158</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.1.58" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 4.4.23" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 4, 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 5.1.69" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. V, 1, 69</bibl>.
<lb />c) to forbid: <cit><quote>hath he seen majesty? Isis else d.!</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 3.3.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 3, 46</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>heaven d. your good souls that you think . . .,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.267" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 267</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>God d. the lute should be like the case,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.98" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 98</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.18" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.81" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 7, 81</bibl> (Qq <emph>forbid</emph>). <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.81" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 7, 81</bibl> <cit><quote>God d. but God should go before such villains,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 4.2.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado IV, 2, 21</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>God d. but still I should stand so,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.3.38" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 3, 38</bibl></cit>.
<lb />2) intr. to be prepared against attack, to make armaments: <cit><quote>lay down our proportions to d. against the Scot,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.137" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 137</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>